title: cannot import name 'DenseData' and 'visualize' from 'shap'
body:
When running the example code (https://libraries.io/pypi/shap):

```
from shap import KernelExplainer, DenseData, visualize, initjs
from sklearn import datasets,neighbors
from numpy import random, arange

## print the JS visualization code to the notebook
initjs()

## train a k-nearest neighbors classifier on a random subset 
iris = datasets.load_iris()
random.seed(2)
inds = arange(len(iris.target))
random.shuffle(inds)
knn = neighbors.KNeighborsClassifier()
knn.fit(iris.data, iris.target == 0)

## use Shap to explain a single prediction
background = DenseData(iris.data[inds[:100],:], iris.feature_names) # name the features
explainer = KernelExplainer(knn.predict, background, nsamples=100)
x = iris.data[inds[102:103],:]
visualize(explainer.explain(x))
```




I got the following errors:

ImportError                               Traceback (most recent call last)
~\AppData\Local\Temp/ipykernel_13492/3852576576.py in <module>
----> 1 from shap import DenseData

ImportError: cannot import name 'DenseData' from 'shap' (C:\ProgramData\Anaconda3\lib\site-packages\shap\__init__.py)

ImportError                               Traceback (most recent call last)
~\AppData\Local\Temp/ipykernel_13492/1790835437.py in <module>
----> 1 from shap import visualize

ImportError: cannot import name 'visualize' from 'shap' (C:\ProgramData\Anaconda3\lib\site-packages\shap\__init__.py)
